                        <h2 class="page-title" text-center>About Me</h2>
                        <div class="marker">a</div>
                    </div>
                    <p class='subtitle'>Hi, I'm Camby Abell, an SDET/SWE from Wilmington, NC.</p>
                    <p class="info"> I have been an SDET for four years, and I absolutely love doing it. I discovered my affinity for automated testing
                        in college during my studies. We had a class project where we had to effectively emulate a modern software company. We had to have
                        "standups", meetings, sprints, retros, etc. and one of the requirements was testing. It could have been manual tests, unit tests, or 
                        automated tests. I had never heard of automated testing before this. So I took on the task of automated testing and immediately was 
                        intrigued by what could be done using the tools. Once I discovered it could be an actual career, I knew the path I wanted to be on. 
                        It perfectly mixes my love for software engineering, and my curiousity when testing software.
                    </p>
                    <p class="info">
                        Some of my favorite things to do are play golf, do brain teasers (NYT Crossword, Wordle, Immaculate Grid), 
